The paper focuses on low-light image enhancement and object detection, which are both sub-fields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of hand-crafted and learned features, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The dataset creation and analysis of low-light effects on object detection can also be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
